  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">INCLUSION I</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Vietnam):  .USAID &quot;INCLUSION&quot; project partners with three Vietnamese non-governmental organizations to implement a comprehensive intervention program aimed at improving the quality of life for persons with disabilities (PWD) in provinces heavily sprayed with Agent Orange...Using FY 2020 funds, the Center for Community Health, Research and Development (CCRD) will focus its efforts in Kom Tum and Binh Dinh provinces. Working through its sub-awardees, INCLUSION will build a multi-disciplinary rehabilitation service system and provide rehabilitation services to PWDs and home-based care and training to family members in nursing, nutrition, and safety. The activity will also work to promote PWDs&apos; social participation, build their independent living skills, and provide peer support and psychological support to family members. Disability policies and their implementation will be advanced through strengthening a few efforts including revision of current policies, advocacy campaigns for the inclusion of anti-discrimination clauses, or development of new guidance for disabilities assistance. CCRD will work with government agencies, civil society, and the private sector to support PWDs...This activity implements Congressional directives and supports the Administration&apos;s policy priority to address war legacies to advance the bilateral relationship. By providing direct services to PWDs, the activity contributes to the achievement of the Mission Objective for promoting greater social, economic, and political opportunities for the most vulnerable populations, including those suffering from war-related disabilities. The activity also supports the Journey to Self-Reliance by strengthening inclusion and participation of the vulnerable groups into society and building Vietnam&apos;s public-service delivery system....</narrative>
  </description>
